description:
This repository contains supplementary materials supporting the manuscript &ldquo;Advancing Transformative Agency in Educommunicative Ecosystems: Contributions to Critical Ocean Literacy in Brazil.&rdquo; 
 The manuscript examines how an interinstitutional educommunicative ecosystem formed through the Brazilian Future Ocean Panel (PainelMar) and its Brazilian Ocean Horizon (HOB) program co-designed transformative competencies for critical Ocean literacy and Ocean governance. The supplementary materials document the participatory qualitative synthesis, competency-based learning framework, and Theory of Transformative Agency (TTA)-based scoring procedure used in the analysis. 
 The materials include generative questions, documented educommunicative pedagogical practices, seeds of good practice, learning objectives, knowledge/skills/attitudes competencies, course modules, the AI-assisted and human-supervised coding protocol, the TTA competency scoring matrix, and contextual information on PainelMar/HOB.

